title: Independent Candidate Malik Adeel Iqbal wins PK-48 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): An Independent Candidate Malik Adeel Iqbal has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-48, Haripur-III by securing 41,777 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an Independent candidate Gohar Nawaz Khan who bagged 21,737 votes.
Overall voters turn-out remained 49.79 per cent.
